{Hello Friends! In this lecture, we are going to check 14 unique pawn
structures arising after White's 3rd move Bf4 in the Trompowsky Attack. I have
set the structures according to the variations that they arise in. Apart from
the ideas in the structure I have also added a few model games for every pawn
structure for your reference in the PGN File.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 Ne4 3. Bf4 {
This is by far White's main move. Now Black has two major options. 3...c5 or 3.
..d5 and there are different structures that arise after these moves.} *

