{This is an interesting attacking game by GM Mamedyarov.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 Ne4
3. Bf4 c5 4. f3 Nf6 5. dxc5 b6 $5 {This is an interesting way to challenge
White's c5-pawn. Black does not fear losing a pawn as it will help him bring
his pieces out quickly and give him a good compensation for the pawn.} 6. e4 $1
{White is of course not interested in the pawn and decides to gain space in
the centre.} bxc5 7. e5 Ng8 $2 {a very passive move that was punished by GM
Mamedyarov ruthlessly.} (7... Nh5 $142 8. Be3 g6 $14 {was a better way to
continue for Black. Though White stands slightly better.}) 8. Nc3 Nc6 9. Bb5
Nd4 10. Nge2 {White believes in quick development.} Nxb5 11. Nxb5 Qa5+ 12. Nec3
a6 {[#]} 13. Nd6+ $1 {tearing apart Black's king's pawn protection.} exd6 14.
exd6 Qb4 15. Qe2+ Kd8 16. Bd2 Bb7 17. O-O-O Nf6 18. Rhe1 $18 {[%csl Rd8] The
poor Black king is under huge troubles.} Bxd6 19. Ne4 Bf4 20. Bxf4 Nxe4 21.
fxe4 Re8 22. Qg4 Re6 23. Qxg7 Bc6 24. Qf8+ Re8 25. Qxf7 $18 1-0

