1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 Ne4 3. Bf4 d5 4. e3 c5 5. Bd3 cxd4 6. exd4 Nc6 7. Bxe4 {
White gives up his bishop for Black's knight in order to ruin Black's pawn
structure. This exchange creates an imbalance.} dxe4 8. Ne2 {[%csl Gd4]} Bg4 9.
h3 Bxe2 10. Qxe2 Qxd4 {[%cal Rd4b2]} 11. Nc3 {[%csl Re4]} e5 12. Be3 Qb4 $2 {
This is a mistake as it allows White to 0-0-0 which not only safeguards his
king but also brings his sleeping rook into action.} (12... Qd7 {was essential.
}) 13. O-O-O Qa5 14. Qg4 {[%cal Rg4d7]} Qc7 15. Qxe4 Qc8 16. f4 {It is time to
open up lines against the Black king.} Be7 17. Nd5 O-O 18. Qxe5 $1 Re8 19. Qc3
$18 {White is a clear pawn up with active pieces.} Bf8 20. Rhe1 b6 21. g4 Qb7
22. a3 Rac8 23. Qd3 Na5 24. Kb1 Nc4 25. Bc1 Red8 26. Qe4 Qa6 27. Ne7+ Bxe7 28.
Rxd8+ Rxd8 29. Qxe7 Rf8 30. b3 Na5 31. Bb2 Qb5 32. a4 Qc6 33. Rd1 Qa8 34. Qe5
f6 35. Qe6+ Kh8 36. g5 Qf3 37. Qd6 1-0

