1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 d5 3. e3 Ne4 4. Bf4 c5 5. Bd3 cxd4 6. exd4 Nc6 7. Bxe4 dxe4 8.
Ne2 Bg4 9. Nbc3 {This is another alternative for White apart from 9.h3 that we
saw in the previous game.} e6 10. Nxe4 Bxe2 11. Qxe2 Nxd4 12. Qd3 Nc6 13. O-O-O
Qxd3 14. Rxd3 {this endgame is more or less equal but White seems to be having
a slight initiative because of his lead in development.} e5 15. Be3 f5 16. Nd6+
Bxd6 17. Rxd6 Rd8 18. Rhd1 Rxd6 19. Rxd6 Rf8 {With pawns on both the sides of
the board the bishop is considered to be slightly superior to the knight.} 20.
Bc5 Rf6 21. Rxf6 gxf6 22. g3 Kd7 $11 {The endgame was drawish but White
ultimately managed to win it.} 23. c4 b6 24. Be3 Nb4 25. a3 Nd3+ 26. Kc2 Ne1+
27. Kc3 Nf3 28. h3 h5 29. b4 f4 30. gxf4 exf4 31. Bxf4 Ng1 32. Be3 Nxh3 33. f4
Ke6 34. Kd4 Kf5 35. c5 bxc5+ 36. bxc5 Ke6 37. Ke4 Kd7 38. f5 1-0

