1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 Ne4 3. Bf4 d5 4. e3 c5 5. Bd3 ({A solid, but a bit passive is:
} 5. c3 Nc6 6. Bd3 Nf6 7. Nd2 g6 8. Ngf3 Bg7 9. h3 O-O 10. O-O {0-1 Anastasian,
A-Ghaem Maghami,E/Stepanakert 2004/CBM 100 [Finkel] (44)}) 5... Nc6 $6 {
A risky move. The statistics is pretty discouraging for black in this line.} ({
A rare and awkward is:} 5... Nd6 {1-0 Stefanova,A-Juswanto,D/Jakarta 2004/CBM
100 [Finkel] (43)}) (5... Qb6 6. Bxe4 dxe4 (6... Qxb2 $2 7. Bxd5 Qxa1 8. Nf3 e6
9. Bb3 cxd4 10. O-O Nc6 11. exd4 Be7 12. Bd2 Bb4 13. c3 Be7 14. c4 Bb4 15. Bxb4
Nxb4 16. Qd2 $18 {[%csl Ra1] 1-0 Stefanova,A-Grobelsek,A/Rabac 2003/CBM 96 ext
(22)}) 7. Nc3 Qxb2 8. Nge2 Bg4 9. Nxe4 Bxe2 10. Kxe2 cxd4 11. Qd3 f5 12. Ng5
Nc6 13. Ne6 Rc8 14. Rhb1 Qc3 15. Qxc3 dxc3 16. Rxb7 $18 {1-0 Adams,M-Xie Jun/
Hastings 1996/CBM 57 (22)}) ({A reliable alternative for black is:} 5... Nf6 {
1-0 McShane,L-Sutovsky,E/Pamplona 2003/CBM 99 [Finkel] (33)}) (5... cxd4 6.
Bxe4 dxe4 7. exd4 Qb6 {- 0-1 Stefanova,A-Mamedyarov,S/Wijk aan Zee 2005/CBM
106 [Postny,E]}) 6. Bxe4 $1 dxe4 7. d5 {This tempting continuation is a source
of worry for Black in this line.} ({After the solid} 7. Ne2 {Jobava didn't
survive as well in the game against Bruzon played several rounds later, though
black's play could be definitely improved.}) 7... Nb4 (7... e5 {--> Radjabov,
T-Polgar,J/Benidorm 2003/CBM 99 [Finkel]}) 8. Nc3 e6 (8... Bf5 9. a3 Na6 10. f3
$16 {Kornev,A-Prokopchuk,E/Nefteyugansk 2002/CBM 92 [Tsesarsky]}) 9. d6 {
The whole fight now will be around this mighty pawn. Black must eliminate it,
otherwise he will never complete the development.} Nc6 (9... f5 10. f3 $36) (
9... Qa5 $5 {deserves further investigation:} 10. Nge2 Bd7 11. O-O f5 12. a3
Nc6 13. b4 cxb4 14. axb4 Qb6 15. b5 Nd8 16. Nd4 Nf7 17. Na4 Qd8 18. Nxe6 Bxe6
19. Nc5 Qc8 20. Qd4 $40 {Hodgson,J-Tseitlin,M/Ischia 1996/CBM 54 [Stohl]}) 10.
Nge2 $146 (10. Nxe4 f5 11. Bg5 Qb6 12. Nf6+ Kf7 13. Nxh7 Rxh7 14. d7 Be7 15.
Nf3 Qxb2 16. O-O Qb6 17. dxc8=Q Rxc8 18. Rb1 $18 {Speelman,J-Wang Yaoyao/
Beijing 1997/CBM 61 [Speelman]}) 10... f5 $2 {After this move Black is already
losing by force.} (10... e5 11. Nb5 exf4 (11... Qa5+ $2 12. Nec3) 12. Nc7+ Kd7
13. Nxa8 fxe3 14. fxe3 Bxd6 {Despite the fact that the king is wandering, this
position could well be playable for Black.}) 11. Nb5 Kf7 12. Nc7 Rb8 {[%tqu
"En","Find the best move.","","","g2g4","This pawn thrust destroys black's
position completely.",10]} 13. g4 $1 {This pawn thrust destroys black's
position completely.} fxg4 (13... g5 14. gxf5 $1 gxf4 15. Nxf4 $1 {[%cal Gd1h5]
} Bxd6 16. Qh5+ Kf6 17. Qh6+ Kxf5 18. Ncxe6 $18) ({After} 13... g6 14. gxf5
gxf5 15. Nd4 $1 {[%cal Gd1h5]} h5 16. Nxf5 $1 {Black can't survive as well.})
14. Ng3 Nb4 (14... g5 15. Qxg4 $1 gxf4 16. Qh5+ Kg8 17. Rg1 Bg7 (17... fxg3 18.
Rxg3+ Bg7 19. Qh6 Qf8 20. Ne8 $1 $18) 18. Nxe4 {with a crushing attack.}) 15.
a3 Nd5 16. Nxe4 Nxf4 17. exf4 Kg8 18. Qxg4 {White has a material advantage and
strong attack as well. Black could resign already.} h5 19. Qg3 b5 20. Rg1 Rh6
21. O-O-O Kh8 22. Nxc5 b4 23. axb4 Rxb4 24. d7 Rc4 25. N5xe6 1-0

