{[#] This is the first important structure for the variation. We can reach it
after 1.d4 Nf6 2.Bg5 e6 3.e4 h6 4.Bxf6 Qxf6 5.c3. White is trying to build a
strong centre by means of Bd3 followed by f2-f4. At the beginning of our
survey, we will examine the positions in which Black does not fight for the
centre. In this case, White enjoys a tremendous space advantage and his attack
can be very powerful.}  *

[Event "Titled Tuesday intern op 2nd May"]
[Site "Chess.com INT"]
[Date "2015.05.05"]
[Round "5"]
[White "Nakamura, Hikaru"]
[Black "Katz, Alexander R"]
[Result "1-0"]
[ECO "A45"]
[WhiteElo "2832"]
[BlackElo "2401"]
[Annotator "GM Grigor Grigorov"]
[PlyCount "79"]
[EventDate "2015.05.05"]
[EventType "swiss (blitz)"]
[EventRounds "9"]
[EventCountry "USA"]
[SourceTitle "EXT 2021"]
