{[%csl Rf5][%cal Gg7g5] [#] Many players try to prevent White from executing
the advance f2-f4 by playing ...e6-e5 and ...g7-g5. From a positional point of
view, this approach is wrong. As you will see in the next model game, Black
cannot compensate for the weak f5-square.}  *

