{[#] This is the most important pawn structure that you should know. Black
fights for the centre with ...e6-e5 and develops his dark-squared bishop on g7.
After consolidating, Black will be trying to prove the long-term advantage of
his bishop pair. White has two main ways to handle the position: 1) gain space
with f4-f5 2) keep the tension as long as possible}  *

