{[%csl Gc3] [#] This structure might arise when instead of 5.c3, White plays 5.
Nc3. Black's main idea is to provoke the move dxe5 by putting pressure on the
d4-pawn. One of the main ways to do so is the manoeuvre...Be7-d8-b6. In the
long-term, his bishop pair might become very effective. On the other hand,
White's most promising plan is d4-d5 followed by the preparation of the
advance f2-f4.}  *

