.c6 is completely playable, I think that more ambitious players would prefer 5.
..Bb4. In this game, we will see how to handle the French type of structure
that might arise.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 e6 3. e4 h6 4. Bxf6 Qxf6 5. Nc3 Bb4 {
The most solid move.} 6. Qd2 {is the main line according to the database.} (6.
a3 {was a favourite move of Chinese grandmaster Zhang Zhong. This seems
strange to me because White gets an inferior pawn structure and nothing in
return.} Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 d6 {As usual after the exchange of the bishop, we place
our pawns on the dark squares.} 8. Bd3 e5 9. Ne2 Nc6 10. O-O O-O 11. Bc4 Na5
12. Ba2 Be6 13. Bxe6 fxe6 14. Qd3 Qg5 15. g3 b6 $15 {If someone is better it
should be Black. 0-1 (50) Zhang, P (2616)-Wang, Y (2736) Jinzhou 2009}) 6... d5
