{[#] This is one of the most favourable structures that White might get in
Trompowsky. We usually reach it after 1.d4 Nf6 2.Bg5 e6 3.e4 c5 4.d5 h6 5.Bxf6
Qxf6 6.Nc3. In order to prevent White's central expansion, Black usually plays
...d7-d6 followed by ...e6-e5. In this way, we get a structure that is similar
to KID. The main difference is that the c4-square is now available for the
white knight. As you will see in the following model game, this difference
favours White.}  *

[Event "Titled Tuesday intern op 9th June"]
[Site "Chess.com INT"]
[Date "2020.06.09"]
