{[#] This is one of the most important structures that you should know in the
systems based on e2-e3. Black's setup reminds the Hedgehog. In the model games,
I examine two main approaches that Black might use: 1) play ...d7-d6 followed
by ...Nbd7 2) play ...Nc6 and keep the knight on d7 I think that in both cases,
White can create at least practical problems for his opponent.}  *

[Event "EU-chT (Men) 19th"]
[Site "Warsaw"]
[Date "2013.11.17"]
[Round "9.3"]
[White "Andreikin, Dmitry"]
[Black "Tkachiev, Vladislav"]
