{[%evp 0,47,21,19,24,-1,17,-5,-5,-6,-13,-18,11,2,40,18,18,21,21,-120,-120,-152,
-152,-152,-77,-110,-77,-34,55,127,244,289,1775,1841,29991,968,29989,29990,
29991,1978,29991,29992,29993,806,979,979,29993,29994,29995,29996]} 1. d4 Nf6 2.
Bg5 c5 3. Bxf6 gxf6 4. d5 Qb6 5. Qc1 {Black has two possible plans in this
structure. First one is to play f5, d6, Bg7, etc.. The second one is the very
ambitious Bh6 followed with f5-f4 which happen in this game.} Bh6 6. e3 f5 7.
c4 f4 8. exf4 {we need to take the pawn, otherwise White can't even dream for
the advantage.} Bxf4 9. Qxf4 {Again White is forced to accept the challenge.}
Qxb2 10. Ne2 $3 {Very important moment. Brilliant move, White needs to know
this move.} Qxa1 11. Nec3 Qb2 (11... d6 $1 {is the strongest move in this
position.} 12. Qd2 {[%cal Rf1d3,Re1g1,Rb1a3] with the simple threat 0-0, Bd3
followed by Na3} Rg8 {Is the most popular reply for Black, but White is
winning anyway after:} (12... Bf5 {is an amateur move which loses immediately
after:} 13. Be2 Bxb1 14. O-O $18 {[%csl Ra1,Rb1][%cal Rf1b1]}) (12... b5 $5 13.
cxb5 a6 14. Be2 axb5 15. Bxb5+ Bd7 16. Bd3 c4 17. Bxc4 Rg8 18. g3 Bh3 19. Ke2
Nd7 20. Re1 $16) 13. Be2 $1 Rxg2 14. Bf3 Rg6 15. Ke2 {[%cal Rb1a3]} Bg4 16. Rc1
{[%cal Rb1a3]} Nc6 $1 {[%cal Rc6d4] the last chance} 17. dxc6 Re6+ 18. Kf1 Bxf3
19. Na3 Qxc1+ 20. Qxc1 bxc6 (20... Bxc6 21. Nd5 O-O-O 22. Qb1 $18 {[%cal Rb1f5,
Rb1h7]}) 21. Qb1 {again this tricky move wins the game} O-O-O (21... Rg6 22.
Qb7 Rd8 23. Nc2 Rh6 24. Ne1 Bg4 25. Qxc6+ $18) 22. Qf5 $1 Bh1 23. Kg1 $18 {
[%csl Rc8][%cal Rg1h1,Rf5c8] and suddenly White's bishop is trapped}) 12. d6
Nc6 (12... exd6 13. Bd3 Nc6 14. O-O $18 {[%cal Rf1e1,Rf4f6]}) (12... Qc2 13.
Qe3 {1-0 (13) Wells,P (2501)-Shirov,A (2709) Gibraltar 2006}) 13. Bd3 (13. dxe7
) 13... Nb4 14. Be4 Nc2+ 15. Kd1 Nd4 16. Qe5 O-O 17. dxe7 {I had a lot of easy
wins here, but decide to prolong the game a bit longer.} (17. Qg5+ Kh8 18. Qh6
$18 {ended the game immediately}) 17... Re8 18. Qg5+ Kh8 19. Qh5 Kg7 20. Qxh7+
Kf6 21. Qh4+ (21. Qh6+ Kxe7 22. Nd5+ Kd8 23. Qf6+ Re7 24. Qxe7#) 21... Ke6 22.
Re1 Kd6 23. Qf4+ Kxe7 24. Nd5+ 1-0

