{[%evp 0,19,18,18,16,-4,1,-12,-16,-16,-16,-16,3,9,20,-23,-22,1,-15,-45,-17,3]
With this game I want to show you how "Mamedyarov's plan" works against
lower-rated opponent.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. Bg5 d5 3. Bxf6 exf6 4. e3 Bd6 5. Bd3 c6 6.
Nd2 O-O 7. Qf3 $1 {White is already much better} Re8 8. Ne2 Nd7 9. g4 g6 10. h4
Nf8 11. O-O-O c5 12. dxc5 Be5 (12... Bxc5 13. Nb3 Bb6 14. Nf4 $18) 13. Nb3 Be6
14. Bb5 Re7 15. Nf4 Bxf4 16. Qxf4 f5 17. g5 Qc7 18. Qd4 $18 {White is
positionally better and a pawn up. The rest was very simple.} b6 19. cxb6 axb6
20. Kb1 Nd7 21. h5 Qe5 22. Bxd7 Qxd4 23. Rxd4 Bxd7 24. Nd2 Bc6 25. Rhh4 b5 26.
a3 Ra4 27. h6 Re6 28. Rxa4 bxa4 29. Rb4 f6 30. Nf3 Be8 31. Rb7 f4 32. exf4 1-0

